events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 32 points and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Sacramento Kings 103-99 to sweep a two-game set on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 32, Lakers sweep 2-game set against Kings with 103-99 win

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony scored 27 of his 35 points in the second half and the Orlando Magic tied their largest comeback in franchise history to beat the Miami Heat 121-114 after trailing by 25 points on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic tie franchise record with 25-point comeback in 121-114 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 23 points and the Memphis Grizzlies, without star player Ja Morant, beat the skidding Atlanta Hawks 128-112 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane and Pippen combine for 45 points, Grizzlies cruise past Hawks 128-112

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 21 points, Collin Sexton and Svi Mykhailiuk each had 18 points, and the Utah Jazz beat the Brooklyn Nets 105-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lauri Markkanen scores 21 points to lead Jazz to 105-94 win over Nets

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 26 points and Evan Mobley had 22 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists, sending the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers to a 126-99 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 26 points, NBA-leading Cavaliers rout 76ers 126-99 for 25th win in 29 games

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored a season-high 43 points, grabbed 16 rebounds and dished out 10 assists for his third career triple-double and the Boston Celtics beat the Chicago Bulls 123-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores a season-high 43 to go with 16 rebounds, 10 assist in Celtics 123-98 win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Bobby Portis replaced Giannis Antetokounmpo in the starting lineup and scored a season-high 34 points, leading the Milwaukee Bucks to a 112-101 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portis scores season-high 34 points in place of injured Antetokounmpo as Bucks beat Wizards 112-101

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 11 straight points in the fourth quarter and 31 for the night as the Golden State Warriors beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 113-103 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 31, makes 7 3-pointers in Warriors' 113-103 win over Timberwolves

events.name: New York Knicks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 29 of his season-high 39 points in the second half to power the New York Knicks to a 104-93 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores season-high 39 points to lead Knicks past Pelicans 104-93

headlines.description: — Quentin Grimes scored 20 points off the bench, 14 in the fourth quarter, leading eight Mavericks in double figures as Dallas beat the Los Angeles Clippers 113-97 on Saturday night despite missing leading scorer Luka Doncic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quentin Grimes leads bench scoring barrage as Mavericks beat Clippers 113-97 without Luka Doncic

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama scored 30 points and tied a career high with 10 blocks as the San Antonio Spurs rolled to a 114-94 victory against the Portland Trail Blazers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama scores 30, matches career high with 10 blocks and Spurs roll past Trail Blazers 114-94

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham scored 28 points and had 13 assists, Jalen Duren added 17 points and 11 rebounds and the Detroit Pistons beat the Phoenix Suns 133-125 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham has 28 points, 13 assists to lead the Pistons past the Suns 133-125
